title: The Frog Prince
sentence: Story There was once a very beautiful princess  ~newline~ And so the princess had many toys and trinkets to entertain her  ~newline~ The princess was dismayed and began to cry  ~newline~ A frog  who lived in the woods  heard her cry and came to ask   What is wrong fair princess  ~newline~ Why do you cry    My ball has fallen into the well  and I cannot get it out   replied the princess  ~newline~    the princess asked eagerly  ~newline~ The princess was disgusted at the thought of kissing the ugly  wart covered frog  but she wanted her ball back very much  ~newline~ After a time  he came back up with the princess s golden ball  and returned it to her  ~newline~  Alright  princess  it is time for that kiss   he said  ~newline~ The Frog Prince     Are you crazy   exclaimed the princess  ~newline~ In bounded the frog  much to the horror of the princess  ~newline~  Ah  there you are  princess  ~newline~ So the frog explained the agreement which he and the princess had made  ~newline~ The princess was angry at the frog for coming to the palace  ~newline~ One look from her father  and the princess agreed  ~newline~ Now tomorrow you are leaving  so just try not to be a pest for tonight   the princess said  ~newline~  Yes  well  I am sure there are good things about living in the forest for a frog   the princess said  ~newline~  Well  don t you live with your family   the princess asked  somewhat impatiently  ~newline~ The princess began to feel sad for the frog with no family  ~newline~ Surely they help you when you need things   asked the princess  ~newline~ Who do you spend time with       Nobody really  at least until you came by with your golden ball   The princess thought of what it would be like to have no friends  or family  or anyone at all to talk to  ~newline~ The princess began to shed a tear for the little frog  ~newline~  What happened   the princess asked  stunned  ~newline~ I have been living in the woods since them  hoping to someday find a princess who could break the spell with a kiss   Both the prince and the princess were happy  for both had learned that it is not good to judge others by how ugly or beautiful they might be on the outside

title: The Frog Prince
